s%20in%20default%20are%20once%20again%20subject%20to%20the%20harshest%20consequences%20of%20failing%20to%20make%20their%20payments%2C%20which%20include%20a%20seizure%20of%20federal%20benefits%20like%20tax%20refunds%20and%20Social%20Security%20checks%2C%20and%20eventual%20wage%20garnishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Education%20said%20that%20starting%20on%20Monday%2C%20195%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ed.gov%2Fabout%2Fnews%2Fpress-release%2Fus-department-of-education-reminds-colleges-and-universities-of-their-obligations-help-struggling-borrowers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefaulted%20student-loan%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20began%20receiving%2030-day%20notices%20from%20the%20Treasury%20Department%20that%20their%20federal%20benefits%20are%20subject%20to%20withholding%20through%20the%20Treasury%20Offset%20Program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20monthly%20benefit%20checks%20subject%20to%20offset%20are%20those%20scheduled%20for%20early%20June%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20department%20said.%20%26quot%3BLater%20this%20summer%2C%20all%205.3%20million%20defaulted%20borrowers%20will%20receive%20a%20notice%20from%20Treasury%20that%20their%20earnings%20will%20be%20subject%20to%20administrative%20wage%20garnishment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20federal%20student-loan%20borrowers%20enter%20default%20when%20they%20have%20not%20made%20a%20payment%20in%20over%20270%20days.%20The%20Education%20Department%20recommended%20that%20borrowers%20in%20default%20contact%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmyeddebt.ed.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDefault%20Resolution%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20a%20payment%20plan%20or%20sign%20up%20for%20loan%20rehabilitation%3A%20a%20lengthy%20process%20that%20requires%20nine%20consecutive%20monthly%20payments%20at%20an%20amount%20determined%20by%20the%20servicer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreston%20Cooper%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20conservative%20think%20tank%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffive-years-student-debt-relief-suddenly-over-trump-default-collections-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20some%20borrowers%20might%20not%20see%20the%20consequences%20of%20defaulting%20right%20off%20the%20bat%20because%20the%20government%20has%20to%20locate%20them%20first%2C%20which%20could%20take%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20lot%20of%20those%205%20million%20borrowers%2C%20even%20though%20the%20collection%20system%20is%20technically%20turning%20back%20on%2C%20they%20might%20not%20see%20any%20consequences%20immediately%20because%20the%20government%20has%20to%20find%20them%20first%2C%20and%20it%20also%20has%20to%20find%20some%20income%20or%20wages%20to%20garnish%2C%26quot%3B%20Cooper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20student-loan%20borrowers%20in%20default%20told%20BI%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-react-default-collections-wage-social-security-garnishment-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20cannot%20afford%20the%20payment%20restart%3C%2Fa%3E.%20James%20Southern%2C%20a%2063-year-old%20borrower%2C%20is%20in%20default%20on%20his%20student%20loans%20and%20said%20the%20projected%20%241%2C500%20monthly%20payment%20is%20not%20feasible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20they%20are%20steadfast%20on%20this%20%241%2C500%20a%20month%2C%20then%20again%2C%20there's%20no%20way%20I%20can%20pay%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Southern%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20come%20and%20take%20it%20from%20me%2C%20and%20then%20I've%20got%20to%20figure%20out%20somehow%20how%20to%20live%20past%20that%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Education%20also%20sent%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffsapartners.ed.gov%2Fknowledge-center%2Flibrary%2Felectronic-announcements%2F2025-05-05%2Frequest-institutions-provide-repayment-informa