EHer%20experience%20with%20Weinstein%20motivated%20her%20to%20take%20a%20role%20in%20the%202022%20%23MeToo%20movie%20%26quot%3BShe%20Said.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20Patricia%20Clarkson's%20career%20was%20an%20embarrassment%20of%20riches.%20Three%20of%20her%20films%20premiered%20at%20the%202003%20Sundance%20Film%20Festival%2C%20two%20of%20which%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Station%20Agent%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BPieces%20of%20April%2C%26quot%3B%20would%20go%20on%20to%20find%20acclaim%20during%20award%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Clarkson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20acclaim%20would%20be%20accompanied%20by%20%26quot%3Bthreatening%26quot%3B%20from%20then-Miramax%20Film%20head%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-life-and-career-of-harvey-weinstein-disgraced-hollywood-mogul-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarvey%20Weinstein%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%2C%20after%20an%20argument%20with%20the%20actor%2C%20promised%20she%20would%20never%20work%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeading%20up%20to%20the%202004%20Academy%20Awards%2C%20Weinstein%20had%20been%20plotting%20an%20Oscar%20campaign%20for%20Clarkson's%20performance%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Station%20Agent.%26quot%3B%20The%20low-budget%20indie%20starred%20Clarkson%20opposite%20then-unknowns%20Peter%20Dinklage%20and%20Bobby%20Cannavale%20as%20a%20trio%20of%20outsiders%20who%20build%20a%20friendship%20at%20an%20abandoned%20New%20Jersey%20train%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Clarkson%20was%20clearly%20the%20movie's%20female%20lead%2C%20Clarkson%20said%20Weinstein%20wanted%20her%20to%20enter%20the%20easier-to-win%20best%20supporting%20actress%20category.%20Clarkson%20pushed%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Peter%20Dinklage%2C%20Patricia%20Clarkson%2C%20Bobby%20Cannavale%20sitting%20and%20talking%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6814c352c6ad288d147fd068%3Fformat%3D